<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN294-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai – tumpai; tuṟai – tāṉaimaṟam. peruntalaiccāttaṉār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>  
    <div xml:id="PN294">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>veṇkuṭai matiya mēṉilāt tikaḻtarak</l>
<l>kaṇkū ṭīṟutta kaṭaṉmaruḷ pācaṟaik</l>
<l>kumaripaṭai taḻīiya kūṟṟuviṉai yāṭavar</l>
<l>tamarpiṟa raṟiyā vamarmayaṅ kaḻuvat</l>
<l>tiṟaiyum peyarun tōṟṟi numaru</l>
<l>ṇāṇmuṟai taputtīr vammi ṉīṅkeṉap</l>
<l>pōrmalain toruciṟai niṟpa yāvaru</l>
<l>maravumiḻ maṇiyiṟ kuṟukār</l>
<l>niraitār mārpiṉiṉ kēḷvaṉai piṟarē</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>While [his] white parasol shines with the light of the moon above,</l>
<l>in the sea-like war camp where they are settled down in crowds,</l>
<l>the men whose work is [that of] Kūṟṟu who embrace virgin weapons,</l>
<l>in the confused thicket of battle where they don’t know their people from the others,</l>
<l>when he, making re-appear [their] master and names, </l>
<l>said “you whose sequence of days is finished among you, come here!”</l>
<l>everybody will stand on one side after having faced the fight.</l>
<l>Like to the jewel spit up by the snake, others will not come near</l>
<l>your husband/relative, on [his] chest garlands in a row.</l>
  
</lg>
    </div>
